00:00:13:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:13:180000.Dialogue: The online description was completely misleading. They said: 8 slots plus removable ID. To any rational person, that would mean room for nine cards.

00:00:22:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:22:030000.Dialogue: But they don't tell you the removable ID takes up one slot. It's a nightmare.

00:00:27:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:27:150000.Dialogue: Do you really need the Honorary Justice League of American membership card?

00:00:33:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:33:090000.Dialogue: It's been in every wallet I've owned since I was five.

00:00:38:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:38:120000.Dialogue: It says, Keep this on your person at all times.

00:00:42:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:42:050000.Dialogue: It's right here under Batman's signature.

00:00:46:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:46:120000.Dialogue: ...and this is Leonard and Sheldon's apartment.

00:00:50:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:50:070000.Dialogue: Guess whose parents just got broadband.

00:00:52:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:52:230000.Dialogue: Leonard, may I present, live from New Delhi, Dr. and Mrs. V. M. Koothrappali.

00:01:05:030000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:05:030000.Dialogue: And over here is Sheldon. He lives with Leonard.

00:01:10:080000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:01:10:080000.Dialogue: That's nice. Like Haroon and Tanvir.

00:01:14:220000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:01:14:220000.Dialogue: Such sweet young men. They just adopted the cutest little Punjabi baby.

00:01:20:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:20:020000.Dialogue: No, we're not like Haroon and Tanvir.

00:01:23:060000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:01:23:060000.Dialogue: So, are you boys academics like our son?

00:01:26:120000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:01:26:120000.Dialogue: And your parents are comfortable with your limited earning potential?

00:01:32:130000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:01:32:130000.Dialogue: It was just a question. He's so sensitive.

00:01:34:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:34:220000.Dialogue: That's my life. That's my friends. Good to see you. Say good-bye.

00:01:41:160000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:01:41:160000.Dialogue: Before you go, we have good news. Put the computer down and gather your friends.

00:01:53:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:53:230000.Dialogue: Is it just me, or does web chatting with your clothes on seem a little pointless?

00:02:01:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:01:210000.Dialogue: The little fat girl that used to kick me in the samosas and call me untouchable?

00:02:05:190000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:02:05:190000.Dialogue: Yes. Well, now she's a dental student at USC, so we gave her your contact information.

00:02:13:040000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:02:13:040000.Dialogue: You're 26 years old, Rajesh. We want grandchildren.

00:02:19:220000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:02:19:220000.Dialogue: If you decide on a spring wedding, we can avoid monsoon season.

00:02:24:190000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:02:24:190000.Dialogue: It's up to you, dear. We don't want to meddle.

00:02:26:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:26:210000.Dialogue: If you don't want to meddle, then why are you?

00:02:28:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:28:230000.Dialogue: If I may, your parents probably don't consider this meddling. While arranged marriages are no longer the norm, Indian parents continue to have a greater-than-average involvement in their children's love lives.

00:02:38:030000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:38:030000.Dialogue: Why are you telling me about my own culture?

00:02:44:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:44:150000.Dialogue: Sorry, but with all due respect, I really don't want to...

00:02:46:230000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:02:46:230000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, darling. We have to go. Doogie Howser is on.

00:03:00:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:00:110000.Dialogue: Neither do I. Doogie Howser's been off the air for like 20 years.

00:03:05:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:05:090000.Dialogue: Actually, I read somewhere that it's one of the most popular programs in India.

00:03:09:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:09:030000.Dialogue: It might speak to a cultural aspiration to have one's children enter the medical profession.

00:03:17:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:17:050000.Dialogue: Excuse me! Hello? My parents are trying to marry me to a total stranger. What am I going to do?

00:03:22:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:22:220000.Dialogue: I suggest you go through with it.

00:03:25:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:25:180000.Dialogue: Romantic love as the basis for marriage has only existed since the 19th century. Up until then, arranged marriages were the norm, and it served society quite well.

00:03:34:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:34:100000.Dialogue: It's the entire premise of Fiddler on the Roof.

00:03:36:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:36:110000.Dialogue: I'm not a big fan of musicals, but I love that show.

00:03:39:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:39:100000.Dialogue: Me too. Of course, it speaks to me culturally.

00:03:42:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:42:060000.Dialogue: Understandable, but there's a universality to that story which transcends ethnicity.

00:03:46:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:46:140000.Dialogue: Let's not forget it's got some really catchy tunes.

00:04:00:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:00:030000.Dialogue: So who wants to rent Fiddler?

00:04:01:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:01:230000.Dialogue: No need, we have the special edition.

00:04:06:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:06:030000.Dialogue: Maybe we are like Haroon and Tanvir.

00:04:32:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:32:170000.Dialogue: This is Dr. Sheldon Cooper. Yeah, I need to cancel my membership to the planetarium.

00:04:40:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:40:150000.Dialogue: Well, I'm sorry, too, but there's just no room for you in my wallet.

00:04:46:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:46:180000.Dialogue: I understand, but it was between you and the Museum of Natural History, and frankly, you don't have dinosaurs.

00:04:58:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:58:020000.Dialogue: Okay, I know you're texting about me and I'd really like you to stop.

00:05:04:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:04:010000.Dialogue: Oh, dear, I am rightly and truly screwed.

00:05:07:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:07:080000.Dialogue: Hey, I thought you were finding new friends.

00:05:11:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:11:190000.Dialogue: In the meantime, listen to this.

00:05:13:220000.Speaker: Lalita
00:05:13:220000.Dialogue: Hi, Rajesh. This is Lalita Gupta. Your mother gave my mother your phone number to give to me. So, I'm calling you and... call me back. Bye.

00:05:26:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:26:110000.Dialogue: Can you believe how pushy she is?

00:05:32:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:32:100000.Dialogue: If I don't call her, I won't hear the end of it from my parents.

00:05:53:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:53:210000.Dialogue: Yes, it is good to talk to you, too.

00:06:03:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:03:140000.Dialogue: Oh, not important. So, anyhow, when would you like to meet? Friday works for me!

00:06:12:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:12:060000.Dialogue: I'll call you with a time and place. But in the meantime, keep it real, babe.

00:06:27:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:27:020000.Dialogue: For what? Making me sound like a Simpsons character?

00:06:30:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:30:150000.Dialogue: Next time make your own date.

00:06:32:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:32:090000.Dialogue: Look on the bright side, she might turn out to be a nice, beautiful girl.

00:06:37:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:37:050000.Dialogue: Great, then we'll get married, I won't be able to talk to her and we'll spend the rest of our lives in total silence.

00:06:46:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:46:110000.Dialogue: Hi, guys. I need some guinea pigs.

00:06:49:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:49:140000.Dialogue: There's a lab animal supply company in Reseda you could try.

00:06:53:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:53:170000.Dialogue: But if your research is going to have human applications, may I suggest white mice instead? Their brain chemistry is far closer to ours.

00:07:02:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:02:010000.Dialogue: I swear to God, one day, I'm going to get the hang of talking to you.

00:07:06:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:06:140000.Dialogue: His mom's been saying that for years.

00:07:12:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:12:160000.Dialogue: I finally convinced the restaurant to give me a bartending shift, so I need to practice mixing drinks.

00:07:17:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:17:050000.Dialogue: Great. The key to acquiring proficiency in any task is repetition.

00:07:21:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:21:150000.Dialogue: With certain obvious exceptions. Suicide, for example.

00:07:32:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:32:000000.Dialogue: We'd love to help you, but Raj is going through some stuff right now, besides, he doesn't drink, so... Really? Raj is going through some stuff right now and he'd like to take up drinking.

00:07:51:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:51:030000.Dialogue: Here you go, Leonard. One Tequila Sunrise.

00:07:53:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:53:190000.Dialogue: Thank you. This drink is a wonderful example of how liquids with different specific gravities interact in a cylindrical container.

00:08:11:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:11:090000.Dialogue: How about a Grasshopper? I make a mean Grasshopper. Okay? Good. Coming up. Sheldon, what are you going to have?

00:08:21:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:21:030000.Dialogue: Can you please order a cocktail? I need to practice mixing drinks.

00:08:24:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:24:160000.Dialogue: Fine. I'll have a Virgin Cuba Libre.

00:08:29:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:29:210000.Dialogue: That's, rum and Coke without the rum.

00:08:38:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:38:220000.Dialogue: And would you make it diet?

00:08:45:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:45:170000.Dialogue: There's a can in the fridge.

00:08:47:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:47:210000.Dialogue: A Cuba Libre traditionally comes in a tall glass with a lime wedge.

00:08:56:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:56:030000.Dialogue: Bartenders are supposed to have people skills.

00:09:01:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:01:130000.Dialogue: Raj, here you go. All right. Who's next?

00:09:04:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:04:220000.Dialogue: I'd like to try a Slippery Nipple.

00:09:17:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:17:230000.Dialogue: Where did my life go, Penny?

00:09:22:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:22:070000.Dialogue: One day I'm a carefree bachelor, and the next I'm married and driving a minivan to peewee cricket matches in suburban New Delhi.

00:09:36:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:36:050000.Dialogue: I had such plans. I had dreams. I was going to be the Indira Gandhi of particle astrophysics. But with a penis, of course.

00:09:59:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:59:220000.Dialogue: You know what? I'm not going to let my parents control my future any longer. It's time for a showdown. Somebody give me a computer with a webcam!

00:10:09:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:09:050000.Dialogue: Sweetie, I think that's the Grasshopper talking.

00:10:11:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:11:180000.Dialogue: And it's about to tell my parents that I'm not riding an elephant down the aisle with Lalita Gupta.

00:10:17:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:17:010000.Dialogue: Okay, calm down. No one can make you get married. Why don't you just meet this girl and see what happens?

00:10:23:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:23:210000.Dialogue: Haven't you been listening to me? I cannot talk to women.

00:10:27:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:27:160000.Dialogue: No, no, let's see how long it takes him.

00:10:31:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:31:060000.Dialogue: Raj, honey, you say you can't talk to women, but you've been talking to me.

00:10:39:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:39:130000.Dialogue: You're right. I am talking to you. Hello, Penny, how are you?

00:10:59:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:59:100000.Dialogue: If you're going to drink on this date, just promise me you won't overdo it.

00:11:07:000000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:07:000000.Dialogue: Freedom? This warm glow inside of me that promises everything's going to be all hunky-dunky?

00:11:14:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:14:100000.Dialogue: Yeah, that. Why don't you bring her to my restaurant while I'm tending the bar so I can keep an eye on you.

00:11:21:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:21:200000.Dialogue: What's the plan here? Let's say he meets her, he likes her, they get married. What's he going to do, stay drunk for the rest of his life?

00:11:41:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:41:170000.Dialogue: I can't believe I'm sitting here next to little Lalita Gupta.

00:11:48:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:48:080000.Dialogue: Little Lalita. That's kind of fun to say. Little Lalita, little Lalita, little Lalita.

00:12:00:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:00:180000.Dialogue: You have lost so much weight.

00:12:03:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:03:180000.Dialogue: That must have been difficult for you because you were so, so fat.

00:12:12:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:12:020000.Dialogue: Of course you do. Who could forget being that fat?

00:12:19:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:19:090000.Dialogue: So you're a dental student. Are you aware that dentists have an extremely high suicide rate?

00:12:27:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:27:160000.Dialogue: Not as high as, say, air traffic controllers, but there are far more dentists than air traffic controllers, so in pure numbers, you're still winning.

00:12:37:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:37:210000.Dialogue: Do you have a drink that will make him less obnoxious?

00:12:40:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:40:190000.Dialogue: Drinks do not work that way.

00:12:43:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:43:220000.Dialogue: I'd say he's doing fine. Look at her. The last girl my mom set me up with had a mustache and a vestigial tail.

00:12:53:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:53:190000.Dialogue: Nothing. I just really didn't want to come.

00:13:02:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:02:050000.Dialogue: In a tall glass with a lime wedge.

00:13:05:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:05:190000.Dialogue: Oh, I'll wedge it right in there.

00:13:10:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:10:020000.Dialogue: So how's Koothrappali... Oh, my Lord.

00:13:16:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:16:110000.Dialogue: I'm pretty sure her name's Lalita.

00:13:18:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:18:060000.Dialogue: No, no, Princess Panchali, fromThe Monkey and the Princess.

00:13:22:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:22:190000.Dialogue: Oh, yeah. I tried to watch that online, but they wanted my credit card.

00:13:34:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:34:180000.Dialogue: When I was a little boy and got sick, which was most of the time, my mother would read it to me. It's about an Indian princess who befriends a monkey who was mocked by all the other monkeys because he was different. For some reason, I related to it quite strongly.

00:13:55:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:55:110000.Dialogue: Sheldon, what are you getting at?

00:13:57:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:57:040000.Dialogue: That woman looks exactly like the pictures of Princess Panchali in the book. How often does one see a beloved fictional character come to life?

00:14:08:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:08:120000.Dialogue: Every day at Disneyland. You can hire Snow White to come to your house.

00:14:12:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:12:130000.Dialogue: Of course, they prefer it if you have a kid.

00:14:16:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:16:010000.Dialogue: Hey, guys. This is Lalita Gupta. Lalita, this is Leonard and Sheldon and Howard and Penny. Isn't it great? She isn't fat anymore.

00:14:25:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:25:040000.Dialogue: Forgive me, Your Highness, for I am but a monkey, and it is in my nature to climb. I did not mean to gaze upon you as you comb your hair.

00:14:35:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:35:210000.Dialogue: You are the living embodiment of the beautiful Princess Panchali.

00:14:39:130000.Speaker: Lalita
00:14:39:130000.Dialogue: Oh, no kidding. Who is that?

00:14:42:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:42:210000.Dialogue: A beloved character from an Indian folktale.

00:14:47:090000.Speaker: Lalita
00:14:47:090000.Dialogue: Us Indian or Come to our casino Indian?

00:14:52:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:52:030000.Dialogue: You Indian. The resemblance is remarkable. I can practically smell the lotus blossoms woven into your ebony hair.

00:15:00:030000.Speaker: Lalita
00:15:00:030000.Dialogue: Well, thanks. I imagine you smell very nice, too.

00:15:04:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:04:180000.Dialogue: I shower twice a day and wash my hands as often as I can.

00:15:10:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:10:220000.Dialogue: But you're a dentist. He's nuts.

00:15:14:230000.Speaker: Lalita
00:15:14:230000.Dialogue: Don't be insulting, Rajesh. So, Sheldon, tell me more about this princess you say I look like.

00:15:21:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:21:110000.Dialogue: It was said that the gods fashioned her eyes out of the stars and that roses were ashamed to bloom in the presence of her ruby lips.

00:15:34:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:34:020000.Dialogue: If you do not stop hitting on my lady, you'll feel the full extent of my wrath.

00:15:40:110000.Speaker: Lalita
00:15:40:110000.Dialogue: And I am not your lady.

00:15:45:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:45:230000.Dialogue: You are my lady. Our parents said so. We are, for all intents and purposes, 100% hooked up.

00:15:51:050000.Speaker: Lalita
00:15:51:050000.Dialogue: Let's get something straight here. The only reason I came tonight was to get my parents off my case. I certainly don't need to be getting this Old World crap from you.

00:15:58:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:58:180000.Dialogue: That's exactly the kind of spirit with which Princess Panchali led the monkeys to freedom.

00:16:07:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:07:090000.Dialogue: Luckily for you-- she could have you beheaded.

00:16:19:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:19:140000.Dialogue: Beats the hell out of me.

00:16:21:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:21:100000.Dialogue: I'll tell you what happened. I just learned how to pick up Indian chicks.

00:16:27:200000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:27:200000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:16:27:200000.Dialogue: What are we supposed to say to Lalita's parents?

00:16:30:080000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:30:080000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:16:30:080000.Dialogue: I play golf with her father. I won't be able to look at him.

00:16:33:030000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:33:030000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:33:030000.Dialogue: Maybe you should keep your eye on the ball, Papa.

00:16:36:050000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:36:050000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:16:36:050000.Dialogue: Oh, now you're a funny man. This is not funny, Mr. Funny Man.

00:16:40:120000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:40:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:40:120000.Dialogue: Dr. and Mrs. Koothrappali, in all fairness, it wasn't entirely Raj's fault.

00:16:44:220000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:44:220000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:16:44:220000.Dialogue: This is a family matter, Sheldon.

00:16:46:130000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:46:130000.Speaker: Leonard

00:16:48:100000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:48:100000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:16:48:100000.Dialogue: Sorry. You all look alike to us.

00:16:52:060000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:52:060000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:52:060000.Dialogue: But he's right, Papa. Listen to him. You! You are the one who ruined everything.

00:16:57:170000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:57:170000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:16:57:170000.Dialogue: Who is it? We can't see.

00:16:59:100000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:16:59:100000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali

00:17:04:020000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:04:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:04:020000.Dialogue: Go ahead, tell my parents why they won't have any grandchildren.

00:17:07:090000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:07:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:07:090000.Dialogue: How would I know? Do you have a low sperm count?

00:17:11:230000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:11:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:11:230000.Dialogue: This has nothing to do with my sperm count.

00:17:14:060000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:14:060000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:17:14:060000.Dialogue: You are wearing the boxers that we sent you, aren't you?

00:17:17:030000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:17:030000.Speaker: Raj

00:17:22:210000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:22:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:22:210000.Dialogue: Can we please stop talking about my testicles? Sheldon, tell them what you did.

00:17:27:070000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:27:070000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:28:200000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:28:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:28:200000.Dialogue: You left with his date. Friends don't do that to each other.

00:17:34:180000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:34:180000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:38:050000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:38:050000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:39:110000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:39:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:39:110000.Dialogue: Sorry? That's all you can say is sorry?

00:17:41:100000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:41:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:41:100000.Dialogue: Take it. It's more than I've ever gotten.

00:17:43:210000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:43:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:43:210000.Dialogue: May I point out, she wouldn't have asked me to go with her if you hadn't been drunk and boring.

00:17:48:060000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.

00:17:51:160000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:51:160000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:17:51:160000.Dialogue: I knew it. He moves to America and he becomes an alcoholic.

00:17:54:150000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:54:150000.Speaker: Raj

00:17:56:070000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.

00:17:58:050000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:17:58:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:58:050000.Dialogue: It was just this one time, I swear.

00:18:03:090000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:03:090000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:18:03:090000.Dialogue: Don't embarrass him in front of his friends.

00:18:06:030000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:06:030000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:18:06:030000.Dialogue: All right. Carry us outside. We want to talk to you in private.

00:18:10:170000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:10:170000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali

00:18:16:230000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.

00:18:20:120000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali

00:18:21:190000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:21:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:21:190000.Dialogue: At least wait till I get into the hall.

00:18:27:080000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:18:29:050000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:29:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:29:050000.Dialogue: Hold on. What happened with you and Lalita?

00:18:33:210000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:33:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:33:210000.Dialogue: We ate, she lectured me on the link between gum disease and heart attacks-- nothing I didn't already know-- and I came home.

00:18:41:050000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:41:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:41:050000.Dialogue: So you're not going to see her again?

00:18:43:140000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:43:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:43:140000.Dialogue: Why would I see her again? I already have a dentist.

00:18:52:160000.Scene: The apartment. Raj is talking to his parents on the webcam.
00:18:52:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:52:160000.Dialogue: I wonder who's going to tell his parents they're not having grandchildren?

00:19:17:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:17:160000.Dialogue: I don't believe it. What's gotten into him?

00:19:19:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:19:230000.Dialogue: Oh, maybe a couple virgin Cuba Libres that turned out to be kind of slutty.
